@node needs "What u need to know"
AllAddType is simply of use. You just know what hexadecimal view of a
file means (try 1> type hex yourfile). You must be able to extract the type
recognition of a file too.
@endnode

@node options "Options"
KEY/A - the type string
TYPE/A - the label
TYPESFILE - the file of types (if you omit it, the file is ENV:All.prefs)
@endnode

@node special "Special information"
- don't use ';', 'ÿ' characters in KEY argument
- ? means any character (like AmigaDOS ? pattern)
- to specify an unprintable character (like [ENTER]=10) use | command (like
  |010)
@endnode

@node usage "Examples of usage"
1> AllAddType MZ                            "PC EXE"
1> AllAddType @?atabase                     GUIDE
1> AllAddType @?ATABASE                     GUIDE
1> AllAddType |015?|000?                    "OS FONT"
1> AllAddType |000|000|000|020              "OS METRC"
1> AllAddType XPKF????????????@?atabase     "XPK GUID"    ENV:AllXPK.prefs

Send me the new types you'll enter (just send the AllAddType commands you
used) and all users will enjoy that.
@endnode
